The article is a transcript of President Joe Biden's speech at the White House honoring American Olympians and Paralympians who competed in the Tokyo and Beijing Games. The President expresses his admiration for the athletes and their incredible achievements. He talks about how the pandemic made training and competing challenging, but the athletes persevered and inspired people around the world. The President emphasizes the importance of never giving up and how the athletes represent the spirit of America. He also mentions the unity that sports brings to the nation, regardless of political divisions. The President introduces Elana Meyers Taylor, a decorated bobsledder, who represents her fellow Olympians and the country.